-- Germany to Planned Increase in Energy Tax by $1.6 Billion, Schaeuble Says
-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 2010-10-26T13:34:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/germany-to-cut-1-6-billion-from-planned-energy-tax-hike-ministry-says.html
The German government is proposing
to scale back a planned increase in energy taxes for industry by
550 million euros next year and by 580 million euros per year
between 2012 and 2014, Finance Minister Wolfgang Schaeuble said
in a letter to German coalition lawmakers released by his
ministry today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tony Czuczka at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net  